{"word":"Jonah or Jonas","slug":"jonah-or-jonas","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Jonah or Jonas</b> - son of Amittai a prophet<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=14&verse=25'>2Ki 14:25</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=1&verse=1'>Jon 1:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=2&verse=1'>Jon 2:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=3&verse=1'>Jon 3:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=4&verse=5'>Jon 4:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=12&verse=39'>Mat 12:39</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=16&verse=4'>Mat 16:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=42&chapter=11&verse=29'>Luk 11:29</a><p/>--\"The Reluctant Missionary\"<p/>Sent to a foreign field<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=1&verse=2'>Jon 1:2</a><p/>Sought to flee from an unwelcome duty<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=1&verse=3'>Jon 1:3</a><p/>Overtaken in his flight<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=1&verse=4'>Jon 1:4-17</a><p/>Finds God's presence even in the depths of the sea<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=19&chapter=139&verse=10'>Psa 139:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=2&verse=1'>Jon 2:1-10</a><p/>Proceeds upon his mission of warning<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=3&verse=1'>Jon 3:1-3</a><p/>Disappointed at the success of his own message<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=3&verse=5'>Jon 3:5-10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=4&verse=1'>Jon 4:1</a><p/>Reveals his bigotry in lamenting the repentance of the Ninevites<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=4&verse=1'>Jon 4:1-3</a><p/>Taught a lesson of the breadth of the Divine Love<p/><a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=32&chapter=4&verse=4'>Jon 4:4-11</a>"}]}